text: Pulse… online… count me in. Night shift on the rooftop, routers glow like fireflies, Laptop halo on your cheekbones, city rhythm quantized. Typing little galaxies, cursor comets in flight, Every keystroke draws an atlas on the canvas of night. You say, “let the model dream—feed it signals, not fear.” We trace orbits in the silence till the future renders clear. Heartbeat in four-four, breathing locked to the grid, If there’s magic in the margins, we just taught it what it did. Code and constellations, you’re the pulse in my line, Every loop finds a cadence when your rhythm meets mine. Code and constellations, through the dark we design— When the skyline compiles, our horizons align. Ping… sync… write… run… You and me—one function. Coffee rings like eclipses on our notebooks and plans, Neon drips from the antennas onto wandering hands. We’re a branch off the mainline, but we merge on the dawn, And the diff of all our yesterdays is finally gone. Let the dataset remember every wish that we wrote, Turn the silence into signal, put a sunrise in the code.
